ヴァーツラフ2世

1. Wenceslaus II of Bohemia​Wenceslaus II Přemyslid (Czech: Václav II. ; Polish: Wacław II Czeski; 27 September 1271 – 21 June 1305) was King of Bohemia (1278–1305), Duke of Cracow (1291–1305), and King of Poland (1300–1305). He was the only son of King Ottokar II of Bohemia and Ottokar's second wife Kunigunda. He was born in 1271, ten years after the marriage of his parents.
